# üìù Clean Keylogger

This is a simple and beginner-friendly keylogger written in Python. It captures keystrokes and saves them in a plaintext log file located in the user's `%APPDATA%\KeyLogs` directory.

> ‚ö†Ô∏è **This tool is for educational purposes only. Do not use it on devices you do not own or without explicit permission.**

---

## ‚ú® Features

- Logs every 25 keystrokes to file
- Timestamped entries
- Plaintext log format for easy reading
- Lightweight and minimal
- Easy to run and customize

---

## üõ† Requirements

- Python 3.x
- [`pynput`](https://pypi.org/project/pynput/)

Install it with:
```bash
pip install pynput
